<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Why would you want to siege? What will you get out of it?<BR>					<BR>You will destroy the town you wish to own.<BR>The guild who owned the town will get 90% insurance on all buildings. So they didn't lose much. So what is lost and what is gained? Nothing!<P>Take over the town you say? Here is the conversation.<P>Guild1- We have bested you. Surrender at once!<P>Guild2- NEVER! You will not take my town i have worked so hard to build!<P>Guild1- Surrender or you shall be destroyed!!<P>Guild2- Fine, destroy everything. Ill collect the insurance and you will have to start from the bottom up.<P>Guild1- Fine! sell me the buildings!<P>Guild2- ok, well lets see...hmmm... Insurance + 50%.<P>Guild1- Fine, here you go. <P>Some battle, the victor has to pay to keep the buildings he just conquered. Insurance shouldnt be allowed. It takes away from the value of the building. No one will EVER surrender, Because even if they are completely destroyed they get the insurance money.<P>Time involved to build? You lose it all anyway when you sign the building over.<P>Keep your building and run it within the victors guild? Pay insanely high taxes. Possibly come off the tree of life. <P>Guild2- Sure ill run my building from within your walls, no im not mad you took over my whole town, ill just destroy you from within.<P>I would like(almost)all your thought on this. Tell me another Scenario. <P><BR>Dan,<P>If you could please stay out of this post. I don't want it to goto shit as soon as you make a comment.
