<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Uber Guilds WILL run the land....if they are allowed to.  In UO, my Guild made it our mission to fight these Guilds and we did, very successfully.  <P>The "Uber" folks band together more readily than others, which gives them an advantage off the top.  They also tend to be powergamers as well, another advantage.<P>If people realize that they need to band together early on, they have a better chance to mold their land into their ideal.  Can you run solo?  Sure but you're not only not going to get very far, you're going to be hurting those fighting the good fight.<P>We'll have to see how it pans out.  As far as waging a costly war, it's one of the many considerations of War.  You can't jump on someone when they're weak only to make yourself vulnerable.  I would assume that a Guild large enough to run a successful siege will also be large enough to build and maintain their conquest.<P>To be honest, it shouldn't be easy to conquer and move in.  If it is, one Guild will take over the entire landscape.  Each small conquest and successful holding makes you that much more powerful and it should be difficult and time consuming.<P>I'm looking forward to it, as is my Guild.  It's all about checks and balances.  All things being equal, the defenders must have the advantage.
</FONT>
