<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Question:<P>1.Can you de-commission a building? Will it give you money back when you do this?<P>						<BR>Another scenario:<P>The guild being attacked is totally losing. There is no end near. The sieging guild will have their building destroyed in no time. Can you sell off all your buildings before they are destroyed? <BR>									<BR>But why destroy them if insurance pays more than de-commission them? What is the greater gain? De-commission or destruction and collection of insurance?<P>---------------------------------------------<BR>2. The enemy has taken control of your town and TOL. The building are still standing and owned by the former guild. Negotiations are taking place but going badly.<P>Scenario:<P>Guild2- You are beaten, you don't have many choices in this matter. Lose everything or sign the building over to us for 50% less than what they are worth.<P>Guild1- We will not sign our building over to you! there is no coin value on the time I spent on them!<P>Guild2- Ok, not a problem. I will remove them  from our TOL and beat the building to almost destruction, I will kill all NPC's belonging to this building and let it degrade into nothing. You will gain nothing since it shall ROT into the ground. <P><BR>Is this possible? Will beating a building almost to destruction help it degrade faster? Is there a point in damage where the building will no longer function?
